Israeli Stocks: Alvarion and Shemen Oil & Gas Resources

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-12-08T16:13:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/israeli-stocks-alvarion-and-shemen-oil-gas-resources.html
Israel’s  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  rose for the
second time this week, gaining 0.3 percent to 1,070.73 at the
4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. The index has declined 1.3 percent
this week. Investors traded about 1.2 billion shekels ($319
million) of shares and convertible securities, according to
bourse data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Alvarion Ltd. (ALVR)   surged the most since June 23,
rising 10 percent to 3.405 shekels. The telecommunication
equipment maker said  Canada ’s Xplornet Communications Inc.
conducted successful trials of one of its products.  Shemen Oil & Gas Resources Ltd.  (SMOG IT) rose 2.4 percent
on the second day of trading to 0.21 shekel, giving the company
a market value of 631 million shekels. The shares of the oil and
gas explorer sold at 0.2647 shekel and declined 23 percent in
their first trading day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
